column6: Parent (If this element is for example a bigger version of another, the other ones ID(decimal) goes here. "No" if this element is it's own.)
column7: Properties (Comma seperated list. A : after the property ID specifies the default value for that property after it. None=Element does not have properties. Inherit=Same properties as Base Id)
column9: Name Combobulator (2=In-game selectable, 1=shows up, but not selectable, 0=displays raw)

column10: Gets overwritten with any foreground object you place on it, but still gets saved (in the foreground). Can still be multiselected. Pasting it that way places 16 environment downwards.
The round one used by golf mode. Actually called "Package" in the name combobulator (a different name is used here to have unique names for everything for better API).
